i0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Since last year the 400-ft high service shaft at the Co-operative Group's CIS Tower in Manchester has been entirely clad in 7,000 solar panels, producing part of the electricity consumed by insurance workers within the building - enough for 9m cups of tea. \par \par \uc2 Along with the 19 wind turbines at another Co-op building in the city, it is one of the most visible signs of what the Sustainable Development section of this year's Queen's Awards describes as the Co-operative Group's "outstanding advance in embedding sustainability across its operations". \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 With 68,000 employees the Co-op is nine times larger than any other Queen's Award winner this year. \par \par \uc2 Green and ethical issues, such as fair trade, have long been important to the member-owned group - the Co-operative Bank won a Queen's Award in 2002. \par \par \uc2 However, Martin Beaumont, chief executive, says the previously diffuse moves towards sustainability within the group have become more consistent and joined-up. \par \par \uc2 "We have been working very hard to make sure it is truly embedded," Mr Beaumont says. \par \par \uc2 Within the past year the Co-op has signed a contract to supply all its UK sites - from its 3,000 stores to its headquarters - with "green" energy, and is pledged to cut energy use by 25 per cent by 2012. \par \par \uc2 The Co-operative Bank, meanwhile, offers green mortgages while its insurance arm is offering an "ecoinsurance" policy that gives discounts to motorists with low-emission vehicles. And Travelcare, the group's travel agency, allows holidaymakers to buy carbon offsets at its branches. \par \par \uc2 The Co-op was also praised for initiatives to reduce and recycle packaging. It has opened an in-house recycling centre for its office waste, with capacity to handle 10,000 tonnes a year. An electric-powered lorry travels between various group premises picking up waste. \par \par \uc2 The group won further praise for its ethical investments and its Community Investment Foundation, which gives financial and voluntary support to community groups. \par \par \uc2 The award for the Co-op, Britain's dominant retailer in decades past, comes as it shows signs of a revival. Since Victorian days the co-operative movement has been linked to goals of fair trading and the Co-op believes it can tap into heightened interest in ethical consumerism. \par \par \uc2 "We are consumer owned and we have been working very hard to make sure that our brand is aligned with what worries consumers about how big business trades, in terms of ethics, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and sustainability," Mr Beaumont says. \par \par \uc2 "There are so many areas where we have led the market in terms of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2 A recent poll named the Co-op as the UK's most trusted brand for consumers but Mr Beaumont says: "There is lots we still need to do. It is a permanent journey." \par \par \uc2 Due to retire this year, Mr Beaumont admits to driving "a Mercedes of some description" - but he says it has a full 2.5 litres of engine capacity less than his previous vehicle. "I am on a journey too," he acknowledges.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 55610737\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 genv : \uc2 Environmental News | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | eecz : \uc2 European Union Countries | eurz : \uc2 Europe | weurz : \uc2 Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertal