used of polluting the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . When the company is Newmont, the world's largest gold miner, and it is accused of dumping thousands of tonnes of tailings every day into a pristine bay in Indonesia and local people are falling sick, cheering the prosecution seems natural. \par \par \uc2 But for once the evidence stacks up the other way, and yesterday's acquittal of Newmont's local subsidiary and its chief executive should be applauded. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The water in Buyat Bay, on the northern tip of Sulawesi island, was tested 12 times after the allegations were made in 2004. The only "polluted" sampling was conducted by the Indonesian police. That was credibly exposed as unreliable during the trial. None of the people who initially accused Newmont of endangering human health corroborated their allegations. None of the mud that local \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  groups threw at Newmont stuck. \par \par \uc2 The case was not a complete victory for Newmont, however. Last year it defeated a Dollars 135m civil suit brought by the government, but only by agreeing to pay Dollars 30m over10 years to establish a foundation to oversee community development near the mine. Its costs in fighting the case are thought to be in the same ballpark. \par \par \uc2 Some analysts say that if a fraction of this money had been invested in more extensive \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  projects before 2004 and if New