par\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Winner: Impact Training Development GroupRunners-up: KPMG LPP (UK), SC Johnson, Lansons CommunicationsSupported by: Cambridge Programme for IndustryThe new Learning and Leadership for Sustainability Award is concerned with how leading organisations are responding to some of the world's most significant challenges, from climate change to environmental degradation. \par \par \uc2 In particular it aims to recognise organisations that are seeking to understand the strategic significance of society's broader socio-environmental issues, and give employees the skills required to address them effectively. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The award is in partnership with the University of Cambridge Programme for Industry. "Increasingly vocal and empowered stakeholders expect today's businesses to take into account diverse environmental, social and political issues, many of which are disconnected in time and place," says Mike Peirce, its deputy director. \par \par \uc2 The shortlisted organisations have not jumped on the green bandwagon, but have held enlightened views for many years. The winner, Impact Training Development Group, the global people development company, was founded 27 years ago. \par \par \uc2 "Our values have been in place since we started and haven't changed massively," says Andy Dixon, head of Impact UK. "We are a 'sustainable enterprise,' meaning that we are profit-making, but we like to do things in a way that takes into account the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the community and social expectations of us. \par \par \uc2 "People like working for an organisation that has strong values which fit with their own. They have reciprocated by being loyal and committed to us and have stayed." \par \par \uc2 Mr Peirce was impressed that Impact has cascaded sustainability objectives and targets through the organisation. Large numbers of employees are actively involved in sustainability projects that are aligned to their personal development plans. \par \par \uc2 Runner-up \uc2 SC Johnson\uc2 's strong commitment to sustainability and the wider community goes back even further, to a statement of beliefs issued in 1927: "The goodwill of the people is the only enduring thing in any business. It is the whole substance and the rest is shadow." \par \par \uc2 "Our values and the capability to deliver sustainability are the DNA that runs through the company," says Sallyann Brookes, the company's human resources director for the UK, Australia and New Zealand. \par \par \uc2 "Consumers, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and making sure we have something that can continue for generations to come are at the core of our business. We don't do it because it is a fad, we have always been doing it. It is why people join our company and why they stay." \par \par \uc2 Although established in 1891, another runner up, accounting firm KPMG, has been involved in \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  and sustainability work, both internally and with its clients for 13 years. \par \par \uc2 This is relatively recent, but well before the topic became fashionable. Eight years ago its board took the unusual decision to allow employees to charge two hours a month to voluntary community work, which was soon increased to three and a half hours. \par \par \uc2 One in three employees volunteered last year, contributing 30,000 hours at a cost to the firm of GBP1.6m. "We have invested more than GBP35m in the community in ten years," says Mike Kelly, head of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . "There was initial concern at the opportunity cost, but we have created an \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  where it is OK to volunteer to do something with no commercial return." \par \par \uc2 "Our young, cool and hip staff has an average age of 33 and applicants know that they are joining a firm where volunteering is the right thing to do and they will be actively encouraged to do it." \par \par \uc2 In reality, the figures underestimate the staff contribution, as many staff are able to contribute fully outside working hours. For instance, 100 staff are school governors, but only about 30 charge time. \par \par \uc2 "Learning about social and environmental issues is vital for embedding good management practice within an organisation," concludes Mr Peirce. "It provides a fresh invigorating perspective of the world, helps to foster innovative approaches to a variety of business problems and builds employee skills which are relevant in many situations."  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl