ness yesterday as it promised Dollars 100m (Pounds 51m) towards tackling climate change. \par \par \uc2 The bank said the money would go towards scientific research as well as projects to help people in poor countries adapt to effects such as droughts, storms and floods. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Stephen Green, the banking group's chairman, said: "HSBC will make responding to climate change central to our business operations and at the heart of the way we work with our clients across the world." The bank will divide the Dollars 100m, to be spent over the next five years, among four charities: the conservation charity WWF; the Smithsonian Tropical Research Institute; the Climate Group, which helps businesses cut greenhouse gas emissions; and the Earthwatch Institute, which promotes environmental issues. \par \par \uc2 Mr Green said HSBC employees would be able to participate in many of the projects. These included finding ways to protect big rivers from the effects of climate change, and helping big cities, including London, to tackle the problem. The lessons learnt would be repeated elsewhere. \par \par \uc2 David Miliband, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  secretary, said the donation was "an impressive example of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 ". He urged all businesses to become "good environmental citizens". \par \par \uc2 HSBC's donation follows a spate of announcements by big banks of investments in businesses related to climate change. \uc2 Citigroup\uc2  said this month that it would spend Dollars 50bn over a decade on "green" investments, while \uc2 Bank of America\uc2  said it planned Dollars 20bn of similar investments. \par \par \uc2 Mr Green said HSBC's donation was different from these investments because it focused on the science behind climate change. \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Sir Richard Branson, the Virgin chief, announced a new group of businesses and academics, the Copenhagen Climate Council, which will seek to help craft an agreement to succeed the Kyoto treaty on cutting greenhouse gas emissions when it expires in 2012.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20070531L104.075\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 hksbc : \uc2 HSBC Holdings PLC | midl : \uc2 HSBC Bank plc\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \