ed a head of philanthropy to formalise its activities in that field and to promote \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  through the group. \par \par \uc2 Tanja Jegger, who is based in Zurich, joined Stonehage in February. Her aim is to provide clients who want to establish a legacy or give away money during their lifetime with customised solutions to similar levels of professionalism as the other services the group offers. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The development is in line with a trend that could make philanthropy as fashionable in the UK as it is in the US. This should perhaps be no surprise, given the increasing similarity between the two in terms of the make-up of the rich population, with the self-made increasingly ousting inherited wealth from the top ranks of the super rich. \par \par \uc2 Twenty years ago, inherited wealth accounted for three-quarters of the names on the Sunday Times Rich List. Now it is City folk and business people who make up that proportion. They are more inclined to give away money, as they are not hoarding a declining store of wealth as is often the case with those who have inherited money. \par \par \uc2 The Warren Buffett view that it is unhealthy to shower your children with vast amounts of money has also been influential. \par \par \uc2 "Lots of people now drip feed money to their children to get them used to it," says Giuseppe Ciucci, chief executive of Stonehage, which has Dollars 24bn under advice. They also try to instil in the next generation a sense that they are custodians of a store of wealth to be used for philanthropic purposes, he adds. \par \par \uc2 Mr Ciucci's clients like to follow the trend, he says. "Once they have identified the trend, they like us to make it more practical." \par \par \uc2 He points to the recent announcement by Sir Tom Hunter, Scotland's wealthiest businessman, that he plans to give away Pounds 1bn to charities in the UK and Africa over the next 10 years as the latest example of someone taking up the cause of Aids in Africa. "Someone else might want to do something for the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 ." \par \par \uc2 People like Sir Tom and Stonehage's clients want to see their money put to work effectively through a professional operation. That is fuelling demand for the services of organisations such as New Philanthropy Capital, which analyses charities and advises on which are most suitable for donations. \par \par \uc2 Mr Ciucci says clients always want to know what percentage of the money they donate will go on administrative costs. "They don't want to be conned - they want good governance," he says. \par \par \uc2 All his clients are interested in giving, he says, but about 40 per cent are what he would class as "very active". They typically give away 2 per cent of their wealth each year, although they may also give away a large part of their capital as a legacy. \par \par \uc2 Stonehage will help them define their philanthropic goals and set up a means of achieving them. \par \par \uc2 The first step is to clarify the theme - education, for example, then work out how to measure the impact of giving, and discover what resources someone is prepared to allocate, in terms of both time and money. \par \par \uc2 Implementation could then be through the Stonehage corporate charitable trust, set up in 2005 to channel donations from Stonehage partners, or via a separate arrangement. \par \par \uc2 "We can help with project selection, manage the charitable assets and monitor progress," says Ms Jegger.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20070806S108.115\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpex : \uc2 FC&E Executive News Filter | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | eecz : \uc2 European Union Countries | eurz : \uc2 Europe | weurz : \uc2 Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph