l15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b SN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The Wall Street Journal Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b SC\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 WSJE\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (Copyright (c) 2007, Dow Jones & Company, Inc.)   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Adam Smith once warned against people who "affected to trade for the public good," but apparently Indonesia never got the message. The President is expected to sign a bill this month requiring companies to spend money on "\b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 " programs. It would be the first instance we know of world-wide that CSR is mandated by law.   \par \par \uc2 If you're not sure what \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  is, well, neither are we. The World Business Council for Sustainable Development says it's "the continuing commitment by business to behave ethically and contribute to economic development while improving the quality of life of the workforce and their families as well as of the local community and society at large."   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 CSRwire.com, a business that makes money off the fad, defines it as "the integration of business operations and values, whereby the interests of all stakeholders including investors, customers, employees, the community and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  are reflected in the company's policies and actions." In other words, CSR is just about anything that interest groups, minority activists or now, in the case of Indonesia, regulators, say it is.   \par \par \uc2 In Indonesia, Article 74, as it's known, was the brainchild of one of the country's biggest political parties, the PDI-P, and will make it mandatory for natural resources companies to enact CSR programs. It's unclear why that sector was targeted, though given that it's the NGOs' favorite whipping post, it's not a surprise.   \par \par \uc2 The bill provides no definition of how much money a company has to spend, how it should spend it, or how the spending will be taxed. Article 74 is so vague that lawyers tell us it could apply to any company that uses natural resources; in other words, every limited liability company in the country.   \par \par \uc2 The business community is apoplectic, and more than 30 local chambers of commerce and industry have complained to the national government. Indonesia is home to a large and very active NGO sector, most of which are dedicated to anti-business projects. So it's good to see the private sector standing up to that pressure and publicly opposing Article 74.   \par \par \uc2 We're told that a few top cabinet ministers also oppose the CSR mandate. A stealth tax on business could stunt already-mediocre growth prospects for the world's most populous Muslim-majority democracy.   \par \par \uc2 Yet President Susilo Bambang Yudohoyono is unlikely to exercise his veto since the CSR provision is part of a bill that on the whole does good things, such as mandating that far more companies produce audited accounts and extending the role of company boards of commissioners. Once the bill becomes law, regulators will take over defining -- and enforcing -- what the CSR babble really means. In a country that struggles with corruption, it's a new opportunity for abuse.   \par \par \uc2 Don't get us wrong. Corporate philanthropy is a positive thing, and many businesses are a force for good in their communities through voluntary charitable efforts. Their employees and customers expect it, and the market, too, often encourages it.  \uc2 Whole Foods\uc2  CEO John Mackey has trumpeted the cause of CSR, which just happens to boost his brand of organic food stores.  \uc2 Starbucks\uc2  may sell "fair trade" coffee, but that also allows it to charge $2.70 a cup for a tall latte.   \par \par \uc2 But the most important way most companies serve their communities is by creating jobs and contributing to economic growth. The late Nobel economist Milton Friedman once argued that the social responsibility of a firm is to make a profit. A corporation, after all, is just a legal designation; it's individuals, not paper firms, who have moral responsibilities.   \par \par \uc2 Jakarta has a spotty record of enforcing rules on its books, so even when it becomes law, the CSR legislation may ultimately prove a dead letter. Regardless, Article 74 sets a precedent that other countries might try to copy. That's bad news for business, the consumers they serve and the people they employ.   \par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=weco20070809000054"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility | c42 : \uc2 Labor/Personnel Issues | gpol : \uc2 Domestic Politics | greg : \uc2 Regional Politi