s & Company, Inc. To see the edition in which this article appeared, click here   \uc2 http://awsj.com.hk/factiva-ns\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 SEOUL -- South Korea's human-rights body and the political group of the country's large conglomerates, which have been at odds in the past, are co-hosting a conference on \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  as Korean companies struggle to improve their image.   \par \par \uc2 Today's conference at the Federation of Korean Industries will bring together representatives of the country's business, labor and activist groups and the government for the first time publicly to discuss corporate practices on disclosure, workers' rights and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The federation, known as FKI, has clashed with the National Human Rights Commission of Korea over the body's recommendations for regulations on corporate behavior. "In that context, it is very unique for the commission and the FKI to co-host an event," says Na Young-hee, a director-general at the commission.   \par \par \uc2 For years, South Korean companies have defined corporate responsibility very narrowly -- through participation in charity. As a result, the topic is often seen by Korean corporate leaders chiefly as a cost or liability.   \par \par \uc2 Earlier this month, one of South Korea's leading business executives,  \uc2 Hyundai Motor Co.\uc2  Chairman Chung Mong-koo, received a suspended sentence on an embezzlement conviction after he pledged to donate hundreds of millions of dollars to charity.   \par \par \uc2 Ms. Na said the commission invited several international experts to the conference in hopes of introducing the idea that there are also benefits from promoting \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Several multinational companies -- such as U.S. retailer  \uc2 Gap Inc.\uc2  through its "Red" marketing campaign in which portions of revenue go to charities -- use corporate-responsibility tactics as a way to sell more products.   \par \par \uc2 "The most advanced companies are looking at \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  as a part of value creation," said Aron Cramer, president of Business for Social Responsibility, a San Franciso-based consultancy, and a speaker at the Seoul meeting.   \par \par \uc2 "\b \highlight22\uc2 Corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  has become something that's not just made in the U.S. or made in Europe but is shaped in all parts of the world," Mr. Cramer said.   \par \par \uc2 "It's a mindset and approach that helps companies anticipate the way societies around them are changing."   \par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=waco20070917000060"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-1