lpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b PG\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 B9\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LA\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 English\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (Copyright (c) 2007, Dow Jones & Company, Inc.)  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 One New York marketing firm is taking eco-conscious ad campaigns to their natural \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- the great outdoors.\par \par \uc2 Hoping to tap into the growing number of big brands launching "green" marketing campaigns, closely held Brand Connections has created a network of 500 ad venues near national parks and mountain resorts throughout the country. Starting this fall, the firm will promote the network to marketers as a way to easily reach environmentally conscious consumers.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Some big advertisers have already signed up. Coca-Cola's Odwalla brand is planning a campaign on the network this fall to promote its line of juices, health drinks and nutrition bars at ski resorts.\par \par \uc2 "People who are in the outdoors naturally want to preserve it. . . . Those consumers are looking for brands whose values align with their own," says Chris Brandt, marketing director for Odwalla. Through its marketing, the brand promotes its commitment to the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  by pointing to several initiatives it undertakes. Among them: It uses recycled materials in its packaging to reduce the amount of waste that goes to landfills.\par \par \uc2 In the past couple of years, "green" marketing has taken off as part of a broader embrace of social or cause-related marketing campaigns, as companies try to tap into consumers' social awareness. Spending in the U.S. on cause-related marketing jumped 24% to $1.34 billion in 2006, according to market research firm Mintel International Group, in large part because of green-marketing related initiatives launched by dozens of big brands.\par \par \uc2 The venues offered by Brand Connections -- such as ad space on ski-lift signs, trail maps and the right to distribute welcome packages filled with product samples at hotels or lodges -- have long been available to marketers. But until recently, a big advertiser wanting to buy space at resorts around the country had to deal with a series of small firms that had exclusive rights to sell space at the venues. Over the past couple of years, Brand Connections has spent what it says was more than $10 million to buy up the small firms to create the network.\par \par \uc2 As a result, a marketer can more easily put together a campaign reaching people visiting outdoor areas all over the country, including Vail, Colo.; Grand Teton, Wyo.; Lake Tahoe, in California and Nevada; the Grand Canyon in Arizona; Acadia National Park in Maine; and the Poconos in Pennsylvania.\par \par \uc2 The venues may be as close as a marketer can get to reaching outdoor enthusiasts at play. Advertising inside U.S. national parks is banned by the National Park Service, says park service spokesman Jeff Olson. "People are always interested in doing that, but it is pretty straightforward: We don't sell advertising," he says.\par \par \uc2 Targeting environmentally conscious consumers can be tricky for marketers, experts warn. Such consumers may be skeptical of corporate claims about environmental commitment. "It is an interesting, but somewhat dangerous spot to be in, saying that the companies advertising saving the woods are in fact saving the trees," says Samantha Skey, executive vice president of strategic marketing at Alloy Media + Marketing. "That sort of makes you the \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  police and puts you in an interesting perspective as an advertising network."\par \par \uc2 Brand Connections says it won't vet advertisers buying space on the network for their environmental bona fides. But it agrees that marketers have to be careful when trying to reach eco-friendly consumers.\par \par \uc2 "You've got to do it in a way so you are not destroying what they perceive to be the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 ; if you are providing them with information that they need, as a tradeoff, they will take the advertising," says Brian Martin, founder and chief executive of Brand Connections. "We just need to be careful. They don't want us to billboard-ize their outdoors."\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=wjco20071002000041"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i838 : \uc2 Advertising | iadv : \uc2 Advertising/Public Relations/Marketing | imark : \uc2 Marketing\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c31 : \uc2 Marketing | genv : \uc2 Environmental News | reqrap : \uc2 Editor's Choice - Advertising/PR | redi