y professions have seen significant growth in the number of women employed over the past decades, few think of Wall Street as a bastion of equality, and a stroll around the boy's club atmosphere of most trading floors in New York or London might quickly confirm this impression. \par \par \uc2 But some contend that it is the interaction between men and women that carries certain synergies otherwise lost in a single gender \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . At least, this is what a group of Geneva-based money managers have hypothesised - and they have decided to put their money where their mouth is by launching a long-only, long-term focused equity fund that actively seeks companies with a critical representation of women in key management roles. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Where many recent innovative finance ideas have exploited ever more arcane mathematical strategies to eke out an edge in competitive markets, AMM Finance's Amazone Euro Fund , launched in 2006, seeks to profit from what might seem an obvious, though overlooked, reality: women have a crucial skill set to include in senior management. \par \par \uc2 "Many people ask us if Amazone is an SRI (socially responsible investment) strategy - we rather tend to think it's basic common sense," says Nicolas de Malezieux, one of the co-founders of AMM Finance. \par \par \uc2 In a climate where \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  is all the rage and SRI funds seem to crop up by the day, Mr de Malezieux makes a critical qualification: "Our first priority is making money for our clients," he says. \par \par \uc2 In other words, the world is already changing, and the goal of the Amazone Euro Fund is to exploit one basic premise: that firms with a high mix of male and female managers tend to outperform over time. \par \par \uc2 For example, Mr de Malezieux explains that trends can be seen in leverage, and how a company manages its indebtedness. "From the studies that we've done, female managers tend to interpret risk differently than men do." \par \par \uc2 He concedes that the idea came from one of his female colleagues, Emmanuelle Alleau, now the portfolio manager for Amazone Euro Fund. \par \par \uc2 Ms Alleau, financial analyst and mother of three children, says the idea was born from the simple belief that households with a man and woman at the head can experience a certain harmony of management. So why not companies? \par \par \uc2 In 2005, Ms Alleau, Mr de Malezieux, and other AMM staff, after debating this topic, decided to see if there was any historical truth to the claim. \par \par \uc2 So they devised a sophisticated scoring system whereby companies receive points for having female managers in various roles of responsibility, for certain lengths of time, etc. \par \par \uc2 After having examined some of the historical implications of gender mix on companies' performance, it appeared there was great stock price resilience in weak markets when companies had a greater gender mix at the helm. \par \par \uc2 What took some time to organise in terms of intellectual construct is easy to maintain, says Mr de Malezieux. \par \par \uc2 AMM devised a system that screens about 3,000 listed companies according to predetermined scoring criteria, then narrows that down to about 150 names that are regularly followed, and selects about 30 names that are held in the portfolio at any given time. \par \par \uc2 Turnover is low, and the investment time horizon is targeted at about five years. \par \par \uc2 "Once we screen for the gender balance, we undergo a rigorous financial analysis, essentially like that for investing in any stock," says Mr de Malezieux. \par \par \uc2 Right now the portfolio is about 60 per cent in large cap stocks, 30 per cent in mid-caps, and 10 per cent in small caps, although Mr de Malezieux says there is no predisposition to this mix. \par \par \uc2 "For liquidity purposes, however, should a large cap and a mid cap screen the same for gender balance and offer relatively similar upside from an investment perspective, we'll select the large cap," says Mr de Malezieux. \par \par \uc2 L'Oreal\uc2 , \uc2 Essilor\uc2 , and Hermes are three of the biggest holdings at present, although there is also no predisposition to geographic focus, as Swatch, \uc2 Statoil\uc2 , \uc2 PepsiCo\uc2 , and Pearson (the owner of the Financial Times) are also part of the portfolio. \par \par \uc2 "The selection process is always strategic," notes Mr de Malezieux. "For example, we recently took Banesto out of the portfolio when we discovered that the real estate crisis in Spain was worse than we first anticipated." \par \par \uc2 Amazone Euro Fund is currently managing Euros 16m (Pounds 11m, Dollars 23m), which AMM hopes to grow rapidly once investors have time to recognise the long-term nature of the opportunity. \par \par \uc2 Mr de Malezieux says two types of investors are generally drawn to the fund: those intrigued by its innovative strategy on gender, and those who like its true long-term nature. \par \par \uc2 Ms Alleau notes that for companies in the portfolio, mean 2006 performance boasted an 11 per cent net margin, a 15 per cent operating margin, and a 19 per cent return on equity. \par \par \uc2 Launched in 2000 with a focus on private wealth management, AMM Finance is a boutique money management firm based in Geneva. \par \par \uc2 In addition to Amazone Euro Fund, the firm also advises an equity fund, Ulysses Global, which focuses on innovative sectors such as biotech, alternative energies, water, and so on. and markets a fund focused on central Europe, Novy Fund. \par \par \uc2 Amazone Euro Fund is a Ucits III fund registered in Luxembourg.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20071022S110.238\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 esl : \uc2 Essilor International SA | banesp : \uc2 Banco Espanol de Credito SA | pson : \uc2 Pearson PLC | phrmpt : \uc2 PPL Therapeutics PLC | bncstd : \uc2 Banco Santander SA\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i81502 : \uc2 Trusts/Funds/Financial Vehicles | iextra : \uc2 Natural Gas/Oil Extraction | i1 : \uc2 Ener