 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  or fail to tackle social ills such as binge drinking should be named in new performance rankings, a Tory policy report will suggest next week. \par \par \uc2 A Conservative party working group on \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  will on Monday recommend that regulators draw up indices, rating companies in their sectors. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Examples cited include a Financial Services Authority index assessing the extent to which businesses treat customers fairly. \par \par \uc2 David Cameron will endorse the call to hold companies to account when he launches the report on Monday. The Tories should "be not just the party of business but of responsible business", the Conservative leader states in a foreword to the document. \par \par \uc2 Business has accused Mr Cameron of sending mixed signals, by pledging to "stand up to big business" while also vowing to support wealth creation. \par \par \uc2 The report, headed "a light but effective touch", calls for higher standards of corporate behaviour to be achieved through exhortation and voluntary schemes where possible, saying fresh regulation should be a "last resort". The Tories have dropped a contentious proposal in an interim report last year for "chocolate trading" schemes, akin to carbon trading, for companies producing "social bads" such as fatty foods and alcohol. \par \par \uc2 Recommendations that have made it through to the final report - almost two years in the preparation - include an "advisory vote" at annual general meetings, allowing investors to censure a company for perceived failings to act responsibly. \par \par \uc2 Executives of irresponsible companies should risk a cut in performance-related pay, the report suggests. It calls for companies' remuneration committees to be required to set out "whether and, if so, how corporate responsibility and sustainability are considered . . . when setting annual bonuses and long-term incentive plans". \par \par \uc2 The central mechanism advocated by the report to encourage companies to take action on issues such as obesity, recycling and problem drinking is a "responsibility deal". \par \par \uc2 Cabinet ministers in a Conservative government should be charged with brokering such deals with industry figures, the report recommends. Companies that sign up could be offered a lighter regulatory regime as a reward, while "laggards" would face the sanction of bad publicity. \par \par \uc2 "It would reflect poorly on any party - corporate or otherwise - that did not participate when invited to do so," the report states.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20080315L106.219\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\a